<emphasis box="[326,531,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Halmatettix major</emphasis>
Grant, 1955
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[686,769,943,970]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 16. Halmatettix major Grant, 1955 holotype (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614425/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authority="Grant, 1955" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1955" box="[790,1164,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Halmatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordidus">
<emphasis box="[790,1023,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Halmatettix sordidus</emphasis>
Grant, 1955
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1178,1259,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@24.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 17. Halmatettix sordidus Grant, 1955 holotype (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614427/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[1284,1432,943,970]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref22521" refString="Grant, H. J. (1955 a) Systematics of the Neotropical Batrachideine Genera Plectronotus, Halmatettix and Cranotettix gen. nov. (Orthoptera; Acridoidea; Tetrigidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 107, 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1955">Grant, 1955a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[151,210,979,1005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref22659" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[222,450,979,1005]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref22332" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2021) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 2 January 2020)" type="url" year="2021">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[326,383,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is characterized by pronotum tectate; frontal costa elevated, lateral carinae cristate; antennae with 19-22 segments; pronotal lobes with tegminal sinus absent or weakly developed, ventral sinus weakly developed; brachypronotal; tegmina fully exposed or, usually, only partly exposed (cryptic) or absent; wings cryptic or lacking; middle femora with a short, usually blunt, median dorso-apical spine (sometimes barely indicated) (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[278,426,1123,1150]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref22521" refString="Grant, H. J. (1955 a) Systematics of the Neotropical Batrachideine Genera Plectronotus, Halmatettix and Cranotettix gen. nov. (Orthoptera; Acridoidea; Tetrigidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 107, 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1955">Grant, 1955a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[436,493,1123,1150]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref22659" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
) and the species are readily distinguished by the morphology of the pronotal scapular area and the degree of furcation exhibited by the lateral carinae of the frontal costa (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[1093,1243,1159,1186]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref22521" refString="Grant, H. J. (1955 a) Systematics of the Neotropical Batrachideine Genera Plectronotus, Halmatettix and Cranotettix gen. nov. (Orthoptera; Acridoidea; Tetrigidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 107, 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1955">Grant, 1955a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,871,1366]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
There is some doubt in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[463,595,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Halmatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[463,595,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Halmatettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinction with some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1862" box="[968,1079,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1079,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tettigidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but a detailed study of the specimens allows distinguishing these two taxa easily. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[782,914,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Halmatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[782,914,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Halmatettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a robust taxon and has tegmina lacking or cryptic, tegminal sinus absence or vestigial and no macropronotal form is known. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1862" box="[1092,1203,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1092,1203,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tettigidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are specimens macropronotal and brachypronotal with the wings normally developed, but sometimes reduced; tegmina presence and tegminal sinus always present and well defined, except 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubbell, 1937" authorityName="Hubbell" authorityYear="1937" box="[821,1256,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="empedonepia">
<emphasis box="[821,1088,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tettigidea empedonepia</emphasis>
Hubbell, 1937
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1271,1355,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1644,1668]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1620]" captionTargetId="figure-22@50.[168,1419,181,1620]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 41. Tettigidea empedonepia Hubbell, 1937 (A) holotype and (B) allotypes left lateral view and labels. Photo of type: University of Michigan, Museum of Zoology (UMMZ Ann Arbor), photo modificated from Holger Braun." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614476/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
